Date:  14/2/2004
Source:  Listener (New Zealand Listener)
Author:
Vol / Page:  48
Edition:
Quote:  Where do the sayings "Mad as a gum-digger's dog", "mad a a meat axe" and "Mad as a cut snake" come from? asks Barry Wheaton of Hobsonville... Mad as a meat axe is out-of-your-mind angry. Frank S Anthony used the saying in his classic <i>Gus Tomlins</i> comic sketches of the 1920s.
